parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Gateway Control Module Failure due to Water Damage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gateway control module can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, leading to a loss of control, and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: loss of steering and brake functionality
and sudden shutdown of the vehicle while in motion.

symptoms: loss of steering and brake functionality
and sudden shutdown of the vehicle while in motion.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Recall Repair Delays and Inadequate Solutions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing recalled vehicles and the inadequate solutions provided by the manufacturer can lead to continued safety risks for drivers and passengers.
symptoms: and lack of communication from the manufacturer.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure Due to Low Coolant Levels
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to maintain proper coolant levels can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure in Extreme Cold Temperatures
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure in extreme cold temperatures can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure Due to Metal Fragmentation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Metal fragmentation in the engine can cause catastrophic engine failure, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure Due to Water Ingress
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress into the electrical system can cause widespread electrical failures, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Gateway Module Failure Due to Water Ingress
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the gateway module due to water ingress can cause electrical system failures, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: False Activation of Audi "Pre Sense" Automatic Braking System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected activation of the "Pre Sense" system can cause the vehicle to come to a sudden stop, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or even fatalities. This can also trigger panic attacks, heart attacks, or other health issues in drivers or passengers with pre-existing conditions.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops or brakes without warning
and the "Pre Sense" light appears on the dashboard. This can occur when the vehicle is stopped at a red light
or cruising at a steady speed.
